trans-unit.source: Represents a dictionary of strings that are used to represent the name of an object in different languages.
Adds a key/value pair to the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref>.
An array of key/value pairs.
The key is an object of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
The value is an associated string.
Adds a language and associated string to the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref>.
A value of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
A value of type <xref href="System.String"></xref>.
Removes all elements from the collection.
Determines whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> contains the key/value pair.
The key/pair to locate.
The key is an object of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
The value is an associated string.
`true` if the collection contains the key/value pair; otherwise, `false`.
Determines whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> contains the specified language.
A value of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
`true` if the contains key; otherwise, `false`.
Copies the elements of the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> to an array, starting at a specific array index.
The destination array to copy to.
The index within the source <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> to start copying from.
Gets the number of strings in the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref>.
A value of type <xref href="System.Int32"></xref> representing the total number of strings.
Returns an enumerator that iterates through the collection.
An enumerator that iterates through the collection.
Gets a value indicating whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> is read-only.
`true` if the dictionary is read-only; otherwise, `false`.
Gets or sets the string associated with the specified language.
A value of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
A value of type <xref href="System.String"></xref>.
Gets a collection containing the keys, or <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref> objects, in the dictionary.
A collection of objects of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
Removes the element with the specified key/value pair from the collection.
The key/value pair of the element to remove.
`true` if the element is successfully removed; otherwise, `false`.
This method also returns `false` if item was not found in the original collection.
Removes the element from <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> based on the specified key value.
A value of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
`true` if the element referenced by key was successfully deleted; otherwise `false`.
Retrieves the string value in the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.LanguageSpecificStringDictionary"></xref> for a specified key, or language.
If the return value is `true`, `value` contains a copy of the string that is associated with the `key` value.
If the return value is `false`, `value` is set to `null`.
A value of type <xref href="System.Windows.Markup.XmlLanguage"></xref>.
A value of type <xref href="System.String"></xref>.
`true` if the contains an entry for key; otherwise `false`.
Gets a collection containing the values, or strings, in the dictionary.
A collection containing the strings in the dictionary.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.ICollection.CopyTo(System.Array,System.Int32)"></xref>.
